('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'college canteen is been developed because of us and also the labs are well equiped nw. We have a cofee day express inside college campus. There is also mac outside near highway so you dont need to worry abt hangout places. I''ll give 7 on 10 to this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'the crowd, don''t expect BMM crowd in engineering colleges. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Majority of the students come from villages. 5% are said to be ‘impossible to last a conversation with’. Students say that you cannot possibly hangout with this crowd except if you fall into one of the above categories. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'The technical festival ‘Crysalis’ takes place in September. Cultural festival Arete comes around mid-March. Model rocketing is a novel event in the tech-fest of Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology (MGMCET) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', '1st step of fest is you need to protest if derz no protest der won''t be any fest thats thetruth ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Director of college has been changed hence the from now attendence is compulsory. At least 60% attendence is required. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Students with exponentially decreasing attendance figures such as 30% to 3% to 0.3% have been found to get away easily. So no problems on this front. “Just produce a fake medical certificate and it’ll do the work for you”, says one of their student. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'ok-ok collegeok-ok campusok-ok placementsok-ok infrabut not ok for 90000. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Mahatma Gandhi Mission''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'This college fees are a lot more according to the facilities, faculty, infrastructure, etc. which students want but dont get in this college. Rather, my advice is take admission in Terna, RAIT, BVP which have lesser fees and yet fulfill student''s requirements at least. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Some professors are very rude and strict and threaten students to fail. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'The less said the better. The lecturers are missing half the time and complete their portions in haste later on. Students without personal coaching often find themselves in trouble.  ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Strictly Ok. However there''s a ground for volleyball and cricket. The classrooms are packed and messy at times. However the labs are well organized. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'The construction of college is accused to be illegal. They are fighting in court. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Eligible students are offered placements at some of the best companies like Essar, Polaris, HCL, LG, Sahara. The salaries offered are from 1.8 lakh to 3.3 lakh per annum with an average of 2.46 lakh p.a.. Unfortunately, though, not too many students are eligible. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'placements are also very good......near about 70% people get placed this year....... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering is located on the Eastern Express Highway, close to Everard Nagar at Sion-Chunabhatti, offering easy accessibility by road and rail. It is surrounded by a sewage canal on three sides and marshy areas with slums here and there on the fourth side. Nearest Railway Stations: Chunabhatti (Harbour Rly.), Sion (C.Rly.) and Kurla (Harbour and C. Rly.) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Real bad! You would torture your taste buds. I''d rather prefer skipping my meal than to even dare step into the canteen of Vasantdada Patil College of Engineering! The Chinese food is edible if at all you have to have your meals in there. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'I think canteen is not that bad as compared to many colleges in Mumbai.It''s the best college if you want to study 4 years rather than to enjoy Engineering. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'The only decent and nearest hangout place would be the Multiplexes “Imax” at Wadala and “Cinemax” at Sion. Good restaurants can be found but only in Sion, which isn’t very close to the college. The canteen serves as the regular hangout for most of the students due to the lack of any other joints near the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Dogs move arouand in the college campus with no restrictions although students are not supposed to hangout in college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Most of them are studious. They possibly watch one movie a year and would hang out with friends once in a blue moon! However, there some decent Pseudo-Intellectual people too and yes not to forget the totally “Mawali” crowd. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'college campus is dirty. Obviously a MAWALI crowd is present troubling many of the girls in the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Sports fest - Sports festival,Fusion - Cultural festival,Fission - Technical fest,Tantra - Tech-cum-cultural festival ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Cultural fest or any other event in this college is done on just name sake basis. You cannot enjoy in this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Attendance used to be really lenient for the previous years. Owing to the change in the management and principal roping in, the attendance has become pretty strict. Students are asked to attend 75% of the lectures failing which term marks will be reduced, loads of assignments will be burdened on your shoulders, and for worst cases, parents will be called. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'Average college with the only positive being great placement facilities. Students with no social life would find this college apt and perfect!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Padmabhushan Vasantdada Patil Pratishthan''s College of Engineering', 'I agree with worst points about the college i believe them myself but some of them are really offensive to me do i look like i cant speak in english well and about the crowd all of it is not bad some of them might prove as good acquaintance while you go through the painful and miserable years and all the torture the faculty and principal might give well all i want to say that all of us are not that bad and yup i personally hate this college and i am sorry for myself and don''t wish anybody else will have to suffer the same fate as me, and i even read that some body said our college has something called gauti girls well wise up buddy this college has no girls!!!!!!!!!!! well i give my regards and i dont mean any harm just practicing my right to speech and thank you for reading all this bull crap peace out ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'The faculty at M.E.S. Pillai’s Institute Of Information Technology (PIIT) is really good for a college on the outskirts of the city, with the students and teachers sharing a good rapport. The mechanical department faculty, it seems, is one of the best in (well not technically, but anyway) Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'this college is only for tp no help from seniorsteachers only value for student who are malayalam ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'One massive plus point about M.E.S. Pillai’s Institute Of Information Technology (PIIT) is its Massive campus, which is surprisingly clean by engineering college standards. The washrooms are NOT cramped and do NOT smell like a fart bomb. All in all, it’s a nice environment to study (or not study) in. ', 'Anonymous');
INSERT INTO `collegereviews` (`CollegeName`, `Reviews`, `User`) VALUES
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'No AC rooms or labs (Except computer lab)so during summers for FUpDFrom computer lab, most important thing is that the only printer available for 40 students is either always busy with a long que for printing or out of ink after loads of abuse so get a printer for your own or go to the xeroxx centre outside the college campus, the xeroxx centre in college is like 2 machines for 3000 studentsCleanliness is best part of Pillai''s college.Good Sports and Gymkhana Facilities but dont expect your seniors to give you a chance to play in college team unless you are Very very very spl talent or you are some royal kid.The campus and area is Sutta Paradise with loads of Smokerrrs arouand.Rare sight of Ragging in or arouand campus (atleast for Engineering Or Degree courses No Ragging from what I have seen for past 4-6 Years) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'The placements hadn''t been impressive till recently but they''ve shown some improvement in last couple of years. The college manages to place close to 50% of the students with decent salaries. Of course, those who DO get placed are pretty happy, with companies like Accenture offering acceptable salaries of 3.2 lac per annum.', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'Good college maaaje mein raho study karo and try to score 60% you will surely Get placed.Companies like TCS, Amdocs ,Godrej,Indian NAvy,Persistent, Inscript,Accenturs recruit students .par FEES bahut hai bhai so take this into consideration ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'Located conveniently close to Panvel Railway Station, Pillai’s Institute of Information Technlogy (PIIT) is a cool 10 minute walk from the tracks. If you wish to save even more time, and spend some more money, you could take a rickshaw which would get you there in not more than a couple of minutes. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'The canteen at M.E.S. Pillai’s Institute Of Information Technology (PIIT) is of an acceptable standard, with edible and more importantly, affordable, food. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'canteen food is not all affordable !!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'A major issue here is the hangouts, or rather the lack of them. Most people end up driving to Karnala or Lonavala, both of which are half an hour away. Chilling at Kharghar is an option too, but there’s not a hell of a lot to do there either. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'NO HANG OUT PLACES AT ALL IN 15KM RADIUS, so if you are thinking of bunking then plan a complete day out instead of coming to college and then bunk for entire day. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'The crowd isn’t too bad either- there’s a healthy girl-boy ratio, and the overall feedback is ‘chilled out’. Quite a few students from nearby villages, though. Due to linguistic minority quota, you can expect a lot of Malayalam speaking students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'u have many drop outs so the crowd isn''t smart either! so you can be an instant star if your intelligent or a football player!but come to the college and u''ll notice it is unlike any engineering college, a fun place to be in, chill out and study( if you will do that ever ) :) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'PIIT hosts their festivals Impulse and Kryptogram around February or March, with the cultural fest happening intermittently. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'Sports events,Fest and everything is organized with students'' money.The college doesn''t provide funds for it.Nobody attends the fests anyway..haha. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'Attendance is not really an issue, with 40-50% guaranteeing safety. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', '75% attendance is must ..no saturday off ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'Not a bad college at all, if you live close to it. “TP karke B.E. banna hai toh aa jaana” says one of their students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Pillai''s Institute of Information Technology, Engg, Media Studies and Research', 'college is ok in terms of cleanliness .strict fr first yr and teachers trouble like hellhole in first sem.fst yr timing iz 730-230 so frget that you can sleep well and cm fr college.fst sem result fr yr2010-2011 batch waz 6% so you can imagine thecoandition.most fascinatng thing about college iz every things white i.e.white boards ,white tiled college ,n superstar ceo who wears white shirt ,pant and even white shoes.comps it facult''z good but profs of mech are worse dan ever who cannot ctrl der ego.hf a dozen of lifts in college of which only 2 are working.bt der is full freedom fr students.log sheher se gav (new pnvl)ate hain padne ke liye,people say. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Faculty at Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology (RGIT) in general is average. Some professors have no clue of the subject at all. There are a handful of professors who have requisite knowledge to be there teaching you. Students have accepted the chalta hai attitutde and thus the staff over the years has been the same and less bothered. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'computers professors are worst,they know handful of things, with which they will play merri-go-rouand. Mostly are M.E students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'RGIT''s glass building which looks stunning at the first glance has a balcony/small terrace on every floor. The big green and well mainatined lawn right at the start of the entrance adds to the USP of the infrastructure. It has good quality labs and computers. The campus is also quite big compared to many other engineering colleges. The classrooms are very well ventilated. Library is very well equipped with dozens of same copy. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'infrastructure is owesome.....but too much traffic problem....great issue is that no hostel facility.... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Strictly okay except for 2010 when it showed 80-85% placements. Placements in the instrumentation branch are relatively bad. Some good companies do come to pick students from college but most students are culled and only a handful are placed. In 2009 about 130 students were placed in good companies. About 45% placements in 2007 and 60% in 2008. Infosys is the major taker. Placements are improving year on year, though, so it''s worth the risk. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'placement is comparatively good with av salary of 3.5 LPA for comps.good for comps ,IT,mech then EXTC. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Manjara Charitable Trust''s Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology (RGIT) is located near 7 bunglows, Versova. The nearest railway station is Andheri (W.Rly. and Harbour Rly.). There are many BEST buses available from station for those who do not want to take a rickshaw everyday. The rickshaw ride might empty your pocket by a huge sum. The college does not have a very accessible location especially for those who travel by train. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'RGIT has one of the very good canteens in Mumbai colleges. It is well ventilated and decently spaced. Various food items like Pav Bhaji, Chaat, South Indian and Pizza are the most preferred ones. Prcies are extremely moderate for the super quality food and thus it has always turned out to be a saviour for most of the studnets. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Owing to it RGITs upmarket location, the college has some fantatic hangouts .Versova beach and ''Versova rocks'' followed by Yari road are all very close to the college and will cost a minimum rickshaw fare to get you there. Eatery joints like Kareems and drinking joints like Pop Tates and Sodas have always attracted the students. Lokhandwala is another excellent hangout next to the college where you can expect almost everything under the sun. Movie buffs can look out for Fun Republic (also famous for its Bowling Alley) and Fame Cinemas at Citi Mall. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Crowd here comes from a mixed background. Some come here through reservations, while some others being from rich families, pay their way into the college. The others who land up here are due to their scores in CET. Boys to girls ratio is the same like any other engineering college. Students from the Western and Northern suburbs and South Mumbai are mostly seen in this college. Due to its ''not-so-good'' location, students from the Central and Harbour belt and Navi Mumbai tend to avoid this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Don''t go on the infra guys!! Ask your seniors about the crowd which is the biggest setback... :( ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Zodiac is the main festival of Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology (RGIT) and it has various programs like rock concerts and gaming events. LAN gaming has been held in this festival regularly. The college hosts many inter-college events which is taken part of by many of the other engineering colleges in the area. This gives the opportunity to the students to mingle with students from other colleges. Various technical and cultural fests throughout the year are organized by the technical organizations, i.e. IEEE, CSA, ISA. Its great for sports and extra curriculars. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'It is indeed one big problem that students face. Not 75% but a minimum of 55% is necessary. Be careful with your professors like in any other engineering college (Panga mat lena bhaiyya). ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'This college is too strict about attendace. if your attendance is low dan 75% dey call your parents for meeting . ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'Manjara Charitable Trust''s Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology (RGIT) should not be one of your top preferences but it definitely falls in the top section of the second tier colleges. A good bet for an average or below average scorer. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rajiv Gandhi Institute of Technology', 'If you not get vjti and sp, then rgit is the best college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'RAIT has some really dedicated professors. Over the last few years, the standard of the college has increased tremendously and thus excellent teaching staff have been employed in this college. There are some okay teachers. Communication takes place in English. Teachers are not very strict; but at the same time they''re not into favourtism. That''s about it. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Only drawback is its teaching faculty, so you need to study on your own. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology (RAIT) is housed in a spacious building, part of the huge DY Patil Campus which is home to many other sister institutes. Most of the canteens and faculties are connected internally and there is considerable interaction among people from different faculties. There are close to half a dozen labs (And we mean well maintained ones!). Even though the college is situated in the DY Patil Deemed University campus it is affiliated to University of Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Infrastructure is very much similar to a Huge Mall. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Records are good and average salary offered was around Rs. 3.25 lac p.a. for the previous year. The major recruiter is Infosys. Great progress has been made in the recent years and students claim that RAIT placements are now at par with the best colleges in Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', '164 students got placed in TCS and arouand 16 students in HCL. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology (RAIT) is very close to Nerul Railway Station and Juinagar Railway Station (Harbour Rly) - Takes about 10 minutes by rickshaw.By Bus : By Dadar-Panvel S.T. bus get down at LP Nerul stop.By Bus no. 511, 512, 507, 506 get down at D. Y. Patil Bus stand.NMMT Bus No.44 From Dombivli and Bus No.24 From New Panvel also drop you close to the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', '10 minutes walk from Juinagar Rly Stn. ''STRAIGHT WALK WITH NO TURNS '' ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Strangely enough RAIT canteen (managed by Anna) serves good food at very reasonable rates. Thali, Vada Pav, Masala Dosa are favourites. The ambience has been recently upgraded and now attracts students from every department be it medicine or law and of course engineering. The change has been so drastic that alumni who haven''t been to their college for long, can''t believe it''s the same canteen. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'RAIT is just AWESOME!Everything about it is brilliant. Especially the Engineering canteen food. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'The basement is the site of all underground and nefarious activities. It houses the engineering canteen and the medical canteen. (Medical? Well the engineering and medical colleges are in the same building and engineering guys share a special relationship with the medicals)Off campus: Dosa Plaza, Rangoli, CCD, Domino''s and the DY Patil stadium. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'KFC, Bikaners, Dominos, D.Y.Patil stadium. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'A masala mix of scholars, cyber junkies, diehard headbangers, take-it-easy goers, flunkers, Martians, Gujjus etc. can be found at Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology (RAIT)Life in RAIT begins at 9:00 AM and seems to end at 6:00 PM (People never leave, they seem to fade away. RAIT is never lifeless). People are into Computers, rock music...rock music and computers. Half of RAIT comprises cyber nuts the other half sleep on guitars. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'crowd of RAIT is just great.......friendfull, supportive. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Kalaraag is RAIT''s cultural fest that is purely dedicated to performing arts and English, Hindi and prominently Marathi theatre. HORIZON - the inter-college fest. Niyantran, TECHKNOW, TECHMATE, Whizion are other festivals. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Festivals, Concerts, IPL matches adds sugar in the tea... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'attendance? Don''t need it. If you get good marks in tests it doesn''t matter how many lectures you''ve bunked. Self-study is very important here ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'have you notice that there no info about attendence....coz you dont need it in RAIT. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology (RAIT) is not monotonously boring. In fact it is daringly different. A healthy mix of both education and entertainment. So if you plan to be an engineer with a difference then RAIT is the place to be in. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Ramrao Adik Institute of Technology', 'Deadlines everywhere..teachers will trouble you to death... ghanta fest.. they stop the artists from performing beyoand 9 pm... as strict as Agnels NOW... one of the most depressing places in Navi Mumbai..RAIT! booo!People are depressing too.. first years are involved in lot of politics too! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'A couple of years ago there were pretty good teachers but due to some unknown reasons the staff keeps changing. But now the teachers are Ph.D graduate and experianced. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Its good college ya sum teachers are fresher but they try to teach which you will find in every college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Now, we found this a little disappointing but certainly not the worse in Mumbai. The classrooms have 2 air conditioners each. The labs are less equipped with apparatus; some are faulty and some aren’t even there. There’s no college ground but there are lots of public grounds nearby for sports enthusiasts especially cricket which beats in every Rizvites heart. The toilets often stink; so it is advised that you finish off your stuff at home. The infrastructure is improving though. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'the interior of the college has been improved to a grate xtent ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Each year more than 30 % to 40 % students are placed through this cell. The training and placement cell is active to keep touch with the industry and invites them to come and visit the institute for campus interviews. Mechanical and Civil departments get the best placements. But, there is no guarantee of placements. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'placement cell sucks...jus 8 students got placed this year.. dont go for this college!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Very few colleges in Mumbai can beat the location of Rizvi College of Engineering. It''s off the plush Carter road promenade and behind Pali Hill, home of many celebrities. One might often bump into a celebrity or someone popular. It''s midway Khar (W.Rly) and Bandra (Harbour Rly) but really far from the respective stations. Taking a rickshaw to the college everyday might be a little expensive. BEST bus no. 220 from Khar or Bandra stations and 51 and 56 from Dadar and Santacruz are the most preferred. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'The Rizvi College of Engineering canteen is a paradise for non - veggies. It''s really big; hence airy, well ventilated and mostly very crowded. You can get some of the tastiest food here. The prices won''t be heavy on your pocket and yes, no one brings TIFFIN in Rizvi, so good is the canteen. The seating is very comfortable. Food available varies from Chaat to Chinese, traditional thalis and what not. Don’t forget to try the Bhurji-pav here. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'The canteen is full of bedbugs so enter at your own risk ! You might carry some bedbugs at your home too... otherwise the food is good and reasonable ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'As Rizvi College of Engineering is located in Bandra there are myriad places to go out to. CCD, Barista, Sheeshas, Candies are the closest to the college, less than a minute away. You can reach hill road or linking road in minimum auto fare to find famous hangouts like Yokos, KFC, McDonalds, Falafels, American Bakery, J.Hearshe, Mumbai Times Cafe, Hukkah n Tikkah and many more. There are dozens of Frankie, sandwich and dosa stalls just outside the college at the cheapest rates. Many LAN gaming centres have also turned up here and have become a big adda for the bunkers. Also the famous Tambe Gully for those who like to smoke and dope. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Hangouts are good. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Crowd at Rizvi College of Engineering is predominantly Muslim due to the 50% quota. Overall, the crowd is pretty cool and the fact that Engineering college has Law, Science, Commerce, Arts, Architecture and Management colleges attached to it; means that you might get a chance to mingle with some of the best looking ones (if not engineering) in the locality (the canteen is common for all). ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'crowd is sad..not even a single chick..architecture has pretty gals.. law''s crowd is wannabe...location is good!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'RAYS is the annual sports, cultural as well as technical fest of Rizvi College of Engineering ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Here comes the best part about Rizvi College of Engineering. You can come and go any time you want to, you are your own "marzi ka malik". Some teachers do threaten about attendance but that is just a formality. Years pass on and attendance keeps on falling. It''s no big deal in Rizvi rather it turns out to be a plus point for students who want to study on their own. You can just come for practicals and study at home for the remaining time. So many students score out here. Imagine going to college right from 9am to 5pm and then rest of the evening being spent completing assignments. You can''t even think of studying under such circumstances. Life is simple at Rizvi. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'As said before you can perform well by taking advantage of low attendance criteria (avg 30-40%) and placements are less, as low number of students are eligible. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'Rizvi is a decent college for those score just about average marks in the entrance exam. Not too far from south Mumbai and easily accessible from western suburbs; so travelling is not an issue. A college in which you can spend 4 years with peace and without any interference from the college management unless you end up doing something really crazy. Students claim that teachers are less bothered about students and normally follow a very easy evaluation method, just fill the papers and you pass (not literally though). But there are disadvantages to it as well, so enter at your own risk!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Rizvi College of Engineering', 'I had visited this college 4 admission and by-mistakely happened to bump into a boy.I was the 1st one to say sorry but still received a whole lot of galli''s. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Faculties are strict in their respective subjects but also friendly to share personal problems :) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'faculty are very nice, friendly, helpful ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'college looking nice from out side. But inside construction is not to good. Particularly in newly constructed premises. Office place is not pleasant. Surrouanding area not maintained. Plantation / lawn / Paver Blocks in the front of entry of college is essential. So that the college look very beautiful and pleasant. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'no ground in this college...uhh..i dont like it!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'believe me this collegeeg will allote 95% placement in next three years ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Not too great, with about 30% of the students getting jobs. Wipro is a major hirer. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Lot of travelling problems to the college makes student annoyed everyday. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Place of college is too good.It''s place just to do study, no other things can be done so mostly students are not bunking the lectures and if they bunk then directly go to home. Waterfall is there, but old students are not bunking there lectures for that. Too good place to do your study..... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'The canteen''s food quality is good. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Relatively good canteen with more-than-edible food. Misal pav is an all-time favourite. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'college in rainy season just seems like a picnic spot. The greenary and waterfall is just awesome, just like lonavala. A totally peaceful place to study. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Quite a few of them, actually. There’s a McDonald’s, a Subway, Little World Mall all of which are pretty close by. The huge central park spread over acres of land and built on the lines of New York’s Hyde Prak is also close by (Though its stilll under completion) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Good looking girls in the college. Trust Me! ;-) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'The crowd at Saraswati College of Engineering (SCoE) is decent, quite cosmopolitan. Very enthusiastic and love to participate actively in festivals of their own college as well as other colleges. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'Saraswati College of Engineering (SCoE) hosts an integrated cultural and technical fest called Nakshatra around the end of February. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'festival is the biggest let down . The worst college in navi mumbai . ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'It is a good college...no doubt...but the major problem is in EXTC branch...attendance is strict....Just make some lineancy in attendance matters because students study more at home than in college... college i think should coanduct only pracs and tests...Students get exhausted in travelling...so they sleep in lectures..and teachers just teach to the class room and the benches....Take the students view whether they want lectures or not and then decide for coanducting lectures... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'No problem of attendance(paper deneko aaye to bahut hai)... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'It''s definitely a much stricter college compared to other engineering colleges in Mumbai ', 'Anonymous'),
('Saraswati College of Engineering', 'college is developing... the crowd is good... it has immense potential for development especially the automobile department. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'The faculty at Sardar Patel Institute of Technology is pretty good. They have enough knowledge about the subject to teach and clear your doubts, if any. Not very strict. Students from the reservation backgorund find the teachers extremely helpful as apart from academics, they do help in solving their personal problems. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Do not take admissions in S.P.C.E. specially in Mechanical branch because all the good and talented faculties have left the college ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Sardar Patel Institute of Technology (SPIT) has one of the largest campus amongst the engineering colleges in Mumbai of which SPCE is also a part besides Bhavan''s college and one of the most sought-after B-School in the country SP Jain Institute of Mgmt and Research (SPJIMR). SPITs building is well furnished and the infrastructural facilities are top notch. Lack of ACs might pull it down a bit but the natural environment is a plus point. Overall pretty decent infrastructure. Classrooms are good and washrooms are very much decent as compared to SPCE. Library is very much equipped with truckload of books.The campus also has a hostel facility considering it hosts two engineering, one management and a degree college respectively. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Building needs a little bit of renovation. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Excellent records and scores over most colleges. It is one of the oldest colleges in Mumbai and hence has a fantastic name and a legacy attached to it. Round about 50%-60% of the students apply for placements, while the rest go for higher studies. Over 100% placement record, with many students getting multiple job offers. Students from Sardar Patel Institute of Technology (SPIT) are placed into companies like Infosys, Accenture, Wipro, Tech Mahindra and so on. Average salary is around Rs. 4 lakh p.a. A number of companies offering really fat salaries are also part of the campus recruitment. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Not the best college but better college than VJTI... good placement.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Sardar Patel Institute of Technology (SPIT) is a 15 minute ride by rick from Andheri railway station (W. Rly. and Harbour Rly.) and shares the same campus with the very famous Bhavans college. Due to the ongoing Metro work since the last few years, the roads are in dilapidated condition and don''t be surprised if the autowallahs blatantly refuse to ferry you to the college. BEST buses to the college are equally unmotivating. Students who travel by train, most of the times, prefer to walk while a few opt for the share rickshaw on the SV Road. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Hostels are good and kept clean regularly.. Mess is also good because it''s only closed on Saturday evening ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'The canteen is pretty big as compared to other colleges, but with 7 branches (SPCE and SPIT combined), it seems a little small. The menu is good ranging from punjabi to chinese to Indian to South Indian. There is a sandwich counter as well. The menu is decently priced. Apart from the canteen, great snacks are available right outside the campus and franky, boy!.. that''s a hot favourite among the students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'On Campus: Quadrangle and Katta at SPIT entrance, Bhavan’s ground, Auditorium, Amphitheatre, Lake (Boating Facility use to be Available!!) and you can spot a lot of interesting insects around.Off Campus: Malls (Fun Republic, Citi Mall, Infinity Mall), Loads of places in Lokhandwala. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Being one of the top rated colleges in Mumbai, SPIT has a very studious crowd. Definitely you will meet many nerds and geeks. A bunch of cream crowd can also be expected followed by students from the reserved category. Eventhough it is located in the western suburbs and has a ''not-so-accessible'' location, students from every possible nook and corner of the city are seen here. Good fun loving life. "Khao, Piyo, aur Aish Karo", quotes a student. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Crowd is not at all friendly, everybody is egoistic and not helpful, crowd is a biggest let down, not attending a lecture is sin for them, personally I feel that this college is an average college just enjoying the name and fame of SP tag, students are as good as donkeys, every single person in this college is a nerd ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', '''UDAAN'' - replaced SPACE as the annual cultural Exravaganza, which had a history of 28 years.''NIRMAAN'' - Annual Technical Festival ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'space festival s thebest......agnee band s cuming this year...!!!!the industrial visit is theplus point of college,n placement is decent. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Attendance is not too strict as well. A minimum of 60% of attendance in all subjects is required. Test marks carry more weight-age over the attendance. But with the crowd that you find in the college, most often you end up attending lectures. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Not too strict about attendance (big plus point! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Excellent academics and fantastic placements gives Sardar Patel Institute of Technology an upper edge over most engineering colleges in Mumbai. The crowd is a let down but it''s definitely one of the top 5 priority list of a student. A must join. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'MCA department is strict NO NO.Poor treatment, unskilled and partial faculty.Students are directionless, demotivated and confused.choosing MCA will not at all be a wise decision. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'This is one of the few things students say Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College (SAKEC) is good at. The math faculty is brilliant. The other faculties too are decent (at least in the first year, after that it doesn''t really matter because you get immune to such things). The electronics faculty is quite good throughout. The Computers faculty is average; so is the IT department. Students say some teachers can make life pretty difficult, but that’s always there. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'faculty is medium...some are too good and some too bad(contrast) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'The infrastructure is definitely not breathtaking, but is simple and decent. The campus is a bit small (way smaller than most colleges, partly due to the fact that the ground is a one minute walk from the main premises) but the quality of the classrooms and labs is quite good. Maintenance is good (except for the ground which starves without grass, however the student community is trying hard to change this). Library is stocked with good number and variety of books. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'The college is awesome. It is good for studies with good interior and a decent level of discipline ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Placements are decent. If you have decent percentage followed by good aptitude skills, you most probably will get placed. (stating the obvious, isn’t it?). TCS, Tata Infotech, Reliance Infocomm, Patni Computers are the major recruiters offering salaries around Rs. 2 lac/year to Rs. 2.2 lac/year. More than 50% placements for all departments with Electronics leading. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'placements secoand good thing 4 this college(most are IT companies),co-operation with students ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College (SAKEC) is pretty equidistant from both - Govandi and Chembur Railway Stations on Harbour line, yet students prefer to commute from Govandi. Several BEST buses drops you on the highway which is two minutes walking from the college. Accessibility is not a big issue here. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Ah! The so called canteen... hmmm. Sadly, the canteen is shared by the polytechnic and the degree guys, and being small and crammed , it doesn’t really help! The food found is quite decent. But there are a certain hygiene issuesWarning: The canteen becomes a furnace during 12:15 p.m. to 1:00 p.m. and the crowd will simply get to you. The Nescafe stall separate from the canteen and Desai snakes (Okay, that''s what you hear very often, don''t you?) stall are pretty popular within the camous. These stalls cater good stuff! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Wrong question, my friend! No ''hangouts'' at walking distance but if you don’t mind minimum auto fares, there is Barista, Acres Club, Ambrosia (decent food though it is tiny), etc. Most of the college ‘crowd’ chose to go home instead! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'no hangout nearby..70% students are nerds(or they act like they are) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'The crowd at Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College (SAKEC) is average. It actually depends upon luck but the seniors are really friendly and helpful here. And also you do manage to find a decent, if not great crowd eventually. Loads of Kutchhis though, after all it has 50% quota for Kutchhis.Since 2012, the college has NO Kutchhi Minority Quota. The college now has 50% Jain Minority Quota. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'sakec should change its name to sajec because its only jain minority now not kutchhi ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Nucleus is the technical festival of Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College (SAKEC) held in February-March. Verve is the cultural festival which is held around the same time as Nucleus. Olympus is the Sports festival. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Festival sponsorship is eaten whole by one man, who thinks he is God of SAKEC...the only thorn in the flesh of the colg, without whom the college cud do wonders!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Attendance is a bit strict at Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College (SAKEC). The college generally expects you to keep your attendance above 75%. If you do manage to have your attendance creeping really low, they might just take you to task. It is therefore advised to take the attendance part a bit seriously. Or else if you do know your way up the hierarchy ladder, things might be compromised but a fat chance there for F.E.s and S.E.s (hard luck fellas). ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'ABOUT ateandence they are very strick this is the worst college I ever seennnnnnnnnnnnn ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'Don''t go here even if you get... you will never be at front foot ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shah and Anchor Kutchi Enginering College', 'If you want to ruin your life then join SAKEC. It''s the perfect place for you. The teachers will make your life hell, they will harass you daily if you are in their eyes. The crowd is very fattu. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'HOD’s are highly qualified and have a thorough knowledge of the subjects. The major cause of worry are the temporary staff, who are fresher and trying their hand at teaching. Most of the lecturers are just BE pass-outs and are doing their masters now. Internal marks depend upon your conduct and your rapport with the teachers. Most of the faculties teach in Hindi, Marathi and English. So vernacular medium students have no complains. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'some teachers are hopeless..like Some female teachers always comments on Students dress up..i have my own experience ..they don''t have fashion sense so they goes mad when see any girl in fancy dress...many teachers do partiality in term work...1 teacher is from computer branch ..seriously he is headache ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'The campus is spread over 17 acres, with three inter-connected buildings. Middle building is for office purpose, with new interiors. All computer labs are well equipped, but mechanical and chemical labs are in poor condition. Air conditioned Seminar hall is newly built but it is rarely used.No Hostel facility, instead students manage to share rooms in MIDC colony or nearby. Seniors help to get rooms if you ask. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Placement is a very disappointing department of Shivajirao Jondhale college. Placement cell is there but it is as good as non-existent. There are no on-campus placements as such, but college arranges group campus with other colleges. College also helps students in developing soft skills by arranging some seminars. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'when i was in BE that one mam concern with placements...she just did timepass....no placements, no companies nothing...now we 60-70 students are totally Jobless ..', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Shivajirao Jondhale College Of Engineering is situated on Kalyan Shilphata road. You can reach the college by central railway trains. Dombivali is the nearest station, which is 4 km away. You can travel this distance by sharing auto-rickshaws. They charge you Rs.15/- for the ride, and they’re available only at the time when college starts and finishes. Kalyan-Dombivali Municipal Transport (KDMT) bus no. 55 also run from Dombivali staion, but it drops you 1km far from college. Bus fare is Rs.5/-.From Kalyan Station the college is 6km away. A 6 seater auto charges Rs.10/- and drops you on the highway, about half a kilometer from the college, which takes some 8 minutes while walking. Its little inconvenient but not difficult getting to the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Canteen is just about average, with availability of some cheap, edible food. Don’t expect variety of foods. There’s also a mess for Hostel students, but it is too far from the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'There are no nearby hangouts. Instead students prefer to play football or cricket in the college ground. If you love indoor sports, there’s a gymkhana where you can amuse yourself by playing pool, carrom and chess. Goga Pure Veg is only other option than canteen to eat outside college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Most of the crowd is from Dombivali and they like to call themselves ‘Dombivalikar’. While there are others who travel from various places ranging from Khopoli to Virar. There are some outside university students who are from Jalgaon. Most people come from a middleclass background and some students complain of girls not being fashion savvy. Local Political interference is less in Students council, compared to other colleges of this area. Ragging is strictly prohibited. Seniors are very supportive. There are no reservations or quotas. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Being a girl I would suggest other girls DONT TAKE ADMISSION HERE. Many seniors esp boys are mannerless and dont know how to behave in front of girls. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Odyssey is the College’s annual cultural festival. Tech-fest also takes place in odd semesters. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'In Shivajirao Jonndhale College of engineering, attendance is not that big an issue. But it depends solely upon Principal’s and HOD’s mood. Temporary teachers are not that strict about attendance. If you appear in defaulter list, they ask for a letter from your Parents. In extreme cases parent are called to the college to meet HOD. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'attendance doesn''t matter at all, just complete your assignments on time and you''re done! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'Well, if you stay in central suburbs and have a below average score, you can expect to join Shivajirao Jondhale College of Engineering. The location, placements and the crowd gives it a thumbs down! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Shivajirao S. Jondhale College of Engineering', 'I passed out from this pathetic college long back arouand 10 years now... and I had taken an oath that i would never see this campus. we were among the first few batches where college was just opened and it was in horrible state. Other than Engineering drawing, in my 4 years study, I couldnt find a single person whome I can call sir from bottom of my heart. Absolutely waste quality. One professor used to teach Microprocessor and used to give marks based on number of pages answer written. No jokes folks that was the case. One person used to force to attend his private coaching. Hope he is not there now. I feel ashamed of saying my college name in my organisation. My suggestion is that if you dont get any college then keep this as last priority as it is coming uander Mumbai university. Placement was 0 at that time. you have to literally hop in rainy days to reach that barren land. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'SIES has good faculty. Students understand what they are taught.Very helpful as well (except some teachers). The faculty in a short span has raised the academic level of the college to be a leader among the similar institutions in Navi Mumbai and is about to catch up with the most leading engineering colleges of the University of Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Some faculties here are either crack or have just come for money. If somebody is good then it is the office staff. Otherwise it depends on mood of these teachers. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Since SIES Graduate School of Technology/SIES College of Engineering has recently opened(2002), the infrastructure is decent. Unlike many other engineering colleges, labs are excellent. The campus is also very clean and well maintained. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'campus is very small but clean. No excitement in college.  ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'LandT InfoTech, Mumbai, Hexaware Technologies Mumbai, Infosys Technologies, Accenture, NSE IT, Wipro Technologies, Bangalore, Tech Mahindra Ltd., Mahindra British Telecom, Pune and many more.Minimum Salary offered 1,20,000 p.a.Maximum Salary offered 3,50,000 p.a.Average Salary offered 2,25,000 p.a. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'no good placements in college. Very few manage to get decent package. Rest get very small salary package while most of them have to find jobs in off campus interviews. So if you have a decent score don''t even think of this college. and if you want good placement then stay away from this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'South Indian Education Society''s Graduate School of Technology (SIES GST) also known SIES College of Engineering is close to Nerul railway station (Harbour Rly.) around about 15 min walk or the first meter of the rickshaw. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'superb location and respectable office staff ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'SIES has a good canteen. Enough room and nice food. The South Indian is (obviously) really good, but even the ''lunch'' is quite tasty.The downside of the canteen is that it’s common for all the other coursers like MBA, BSc, Commerce, 11th and 12th. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'canteen is maintained very well with an extra floor for more convince. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'On Campus: Auditorium/Amphitheatre, around the canteenOff Campus: Malls, some RestaurantsYou may find good places in Vashi which is a little far from here. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'A mix of crowd (majority is South Indian, but doesn’t matter).You’ll find both kinds of people here fun-loving and books-crazy. A very energetic crowd makes the college environment vibrant and active. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Crowds doesn''t matter as you can find people from north - south... Sex ratio (6;4).... So you can blindly enter over here if you landed btwn 60-80 composite score... ALL THE BEST... . ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', '''Cognition'' (Technical Festival) ''Tatvmoksh'' (Cultural Festival) are the two festivals of SIES Graduate School Of Technology/SIES College of Engineering ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Many events are organised here and most of them are a result of students'' efforts. There''s a seminar on some topic (of students'' choice) by some reputed speaker once in almost every 2-3 weeks! ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Minimum requirement of 75% has to be fulfilled. Very strict. If the requirement is not fulfilled then papers are to be solved, the number of papers and their length being proportional to the lack of attendance. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'NO one carez bout attendance...just keep it near 60%..stay away if you have scord above 130.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Overall, a decent college with the only disadvantage for Mumbaikars being its location. A good one though for those who stay close from there or those who don''t mind traveling. ', 'Anonymous'),
('SIES Graduate School of Technology', 'Use of mobile phones is prohibited anywhere in the campus. and if you''re caught with mobile in hand, then there''s a fine of 5000Rs. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', '@EXTC pass-out LOL! Very true. Let''s see what the damn professor has to say about that. XD ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Agrred to all the points....the faculty here is only to torture and spoil your happiness..specially extc...college doesnt support their own students.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Picture this - you go to the washroom, and there''s no water but its too late to have realized that - yes, it happens! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Computers for the extc labs dont deserve to be in a school lab. The worst lab is the project lab where profs expect students to make NASA level projects but the computers are rubbish and the antivirus is even worse. The speeds are arouand 10 kbps max. I dont believe in stereotypes and so i''ll tell you some profs who were decent and they are Hariprasad[Decent teaching but understands student problems and approachable],S Thalavoor[decent teaching and approachable]. Go to this college only if its nearby or if you get a college out of Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous');
INSERT INTO `collegereviews` (`CollegeName`, `Reviews`, `User`) VALUES
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', '@--Unnmaned--are you serious? why dont you cite any evidence about this fact? facts are not represented properly.. they only consider students with over 60% as eligible for placements. and what statistics they give you is of those students. What abo ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Placements here are like the stock markets: unpredictable. One fine morning you come to college in nicely pressed formals for interview, only to find that the company you depended on to save your ass (or make your life, depends which way you look at it) has decided to impale you on Seekh Kebab skewers, just becoz your TPO was being a lying bitch. Also, if you enter said bitch''s cabin, u''ll be looked upon like your some infectious disease that shud''ve been eliminated during the Victorian era. My mummy''s old sandals are more sensitive towards people than the placement staff here.The Head of IT dept. boasts he has worked with Intel. Given the kind of geezer that he is, I guess he was employed for housekeeping.Must''ve accidently touched an old 8085uP with his pinky-finger while dusting the place. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'St. Francis Institute of Technology (SFIT) is a 10 minute rickshaw ride from Borivali station (Western Railway) and a couple of steps from the famous Bhagwati hospital. Lots of BEST buses (203, 204, 206, 207, 210, 707) from Borivali station drop you right outside the college gate. Buses are the ideal mode of transpotation to this college. Accesibility to SFIT is never an issue. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Cantenn is worst ever, and has been like that ever since the college startd. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Spot on ..canteen is worst ever! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Forget hangouts...all the money is going in xerox sheets. Actually, I''m woandering to own one. There income is surely greater than engineers..!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'they missed 1 good hangout place - there is a river which flows behiand the college. It is very clean and students can come here to have fun picnic-style ! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'The environment of the college is good and has a good crowd. but you should only join this college if you want to finally eand up self studying your entire portion. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'crowd is too good! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'This college doesn''t have funds to arrange our farewell what a great college ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'festivals are as rocking as it can get! ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'as far as attendance is concern you will enjoy it once you make good friends ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'Worst part is you have to maintain 75% ateandnce, and sit for lectures wher you wil 99% of time not understand a word.... ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'DEAR MR.TPO AND HIS FAT-A** ASSISTANT, GO DIE!! To the effect that Infosys cancelled placement at the last moment.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. Francies Institute of Technology', 'I am not a faculty. Why on earth will a prof come here? They get amazing salaries. Good enough not to bother about the students. Even if he does he won''t be interested in posting a comment here. Well I understand the feelings everyone is haveing over here maybe I''m just in SE and I got a lot more to see. About "actual Position" I just want to say when I was in 3rd sem I got very less term work marks so I worked upon it and did well in my 4th sem. The term work marks are directly proportional to what you score in classtest. Teachers give you the question bank. Most ask the same questions that have been repeated in just last year''s papers. I scored well in this times termwork so I felt that college is doing justice to my hardwork. Maybe you guys are right. What happens in other colleges is different. I have friends in Thakur they are not bothered about class test nor about the attendance and are enjoying their college life and still being able to score amazing marks (infact more than me) because that much tough evaluation no one does. That gives a bad feeling as to why a less deserving student in a lower cut-off college getting more internal marks than me. That''s why I also said don''t take this college and go somewhere else. You got this college on your merit but your merit won''t give you a good college life if you choose to come here. I worked hard I got my termwork corrected. There are students who work hard, very hard but their hard work is not paid and they don''t score well in classtests. So their termwork reduces... in fact suffers but well that does not mean that the student has no potential. and should get termwork like 13 and 14 that''s like very bad. Also about the profs I tell you every subject has two or three profs.. You may get the one who teaches the worse. and has no knowledge abt the subject. Go approach others you will be shocked to see the response.. We often hesitate to meet other profs who don''t teach us. Maybe there are more tough and horrible faculties I still have to face. But till the SE level I feel the college is going normal. I won''t say great.. I''m just justifying what all I have said. As I''m saying there is a lot more to see. You all have passed out so you are giving the comments you feel from your heart I''m still studying and hope few things from college. If you loose hope on the college you will have a very VERY tough time. Imagine me. I''m among you people. This is for those people who are still studing in SFIT I''m saying don''t give up hope if you have positive thinking we will do it. You will pass with good marks just work hard. Don''t compare this college with other colleges once you''re inside it cause you will have a tough time and will be disappointed always. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'Computers and IT dept. have a lot of freshers. Civil has a mix of experienced and novice professors. EXTC has senior staff with very good experience. English communication is quite decent as majority of the teachers are catholic. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'Honestly this a place for a bunch of failures who couldn''t get a job after engineering so they ended up being professors here. Most of the professors are some egoistic kids who need to be pampered if you want good term work. Most of them are involved in their love lives with fellow professors and with so poor teaching quality they demand 75% attendance. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'The building is still under construction. There are rent facilities for students who stay really far. Labs are well equipped and Internet is available. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'Civil and mechanical workshop and labs are very very best....... ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'The first batch is yet to come out and nothing can be commented on the placements till then. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'No placement. No job. No future. ', 'Anonymous'),
('St. John College of Engineering', 'St. John College Of Engineering And Technology is located on the east side of Palghar. If you are a train commuter, then you get share-rickshaws to college from the west at affordable cost. Students also commute via their own two wheelers and college buses. ', 'Anonymous'),
