('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'The teaching staff at TSEC is good and well-qualified. They have proper knowledge about the subject. Teaching abilities, however, vary from professor to professor and depending on your luck, you may get excellent or average teachers. Lectures are communicated in English. All the teachers are extremely friendly and sharing an amazing rapoort witht the students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Yes, some of the faculty are excellent while some are boring. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Thadomal Shahni Engineering College is surrounded by many other famous colleges of the same HSNC board like MMK and R.D. National College and the very famous IIPM (Yes yes, Arindham Chaudhari). Just like many other colleges in the city of Mumbai, TSEC, too, doesn''t have any sprawling campus. It has average classrooms and laboratories. Library is quite good and equipped with WiFi. All in all, the infrastructure is pretty much upto the mark. Lack of AC''s are a huge turn off.There are no hostel facilities. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'The first time I went to this college me and my friend laughed so hard by seeing this building. The building from outside looks like BMC school but from inside it''s still OK. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Thadomal Shahani Engineering College (TSEC) is a renowned college; so placements are definitely good. All the good companies place students with decent salaries. TCS, Infosys, and Accenture are the major recruiters offering an average salary of Rs. 2.8-3 lac/year with highest salary even reaching a whopping Rs. 11.3 lac/year. In short, 100% placements. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'all the things are right except placement......avg salary offered is 3.8-4.2 lacs...this year, highest was 12lacs....!!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Thadomal Shahani Engineering College (TSEC) is located on the very famous Bandra Linking Road. It''s a 10 minute walk from Bandra station (W.Rly. and Harbour Rly.). Hundreds of share rickshaws from the station drop you to the college. Most students prefer share rickshaws while some don''t mind to walk upto the college.Accessibility to the college has never been an issue. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Food is good and edible. So if you forget your dabba at home, sometimes it''s a delight. Comparatively, a very big area and so doesn’t cause much suffocation, even during the peak hours of lunch time. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Just at the corner of Thadomal Shahani Engineering College (TSEC) is JAY sandwich, the most famous amongst all of the sandwich-wallah''s in the town. McDonald''s, KFC, Barista, Bombay (Mumbai) Blues, Red Box, Natural, Subway are other good options with Bandstand and Carter Road as ultimate hotspot. Chappals, branded (read fake) clutches, handbags and exiciting accessories makes this are a huge hit, especially for girls. Guys, too, get their share. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Thadomal Shahani Engineering College (TSEC) has a 50% minority quota for sindhis, so the cream crowd is very much expected. Decent people from good families are expected here. As it is located in the heart of the city, there are students from Central, South, Northern suburbs and Navi Mumbai. General life as such is a very happy-go-lucky types. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'No, there are all kind of students...ranging from average, geeky to scholars.No, there is no cast discrimination! you will be comfortable with your classmates in college ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'The annual intra collegiate event of Thadomal Shahani Engineering College (TSEC) is called Avalanche and is usually held in October. This is done primarily to provide an opportunity for the freshers in college to participate and get to know the college and their seniors better.Isaac (Technical Festival) and Trifles (Cultural Festival). ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Attendance is not a very big issue at Thadomal Shahani but they do stress on it sometimes. So one needs to be thoda attentive and pay heed to warnings, if any, just for the sake of it. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'No, attendance in EVERY subject is not strict while some subjects it is ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'This college is basically built for siandhi people as there 51% reservations for that + some extra vacant seats if someone cancels. Rest all come from CAP ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thadomal Shahani Engineering College', 'Great college and package... seniors are really cool and helpful. All engaged in some or the other society. Though there is a password for WiFi which you''ll have to obtain.. 6th and 8th floor provides free wifi ;) good teachers. Some do take lectures in AC seminar halls... great college. 2nd preference for chemical first being UDCT ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Average faculty. Teachers take the pains to teach and students understand what they are taught as well. The teachers are very helpful. Somehow, the EXTC department students aren''t very fond of the teachers and their teaching. They''ve loads to complain about them. Fortunately, Computers and IT department students have lauding words for their professors. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Extc dept is worst.. faculty is bad.. Agree wit previous comments ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET) has excellent Infrastructure. One of the best in town. Huge campus. You can see the pictures of the college and read its own description about its infrastructure on its official website. And you might happen to spot celebrities if you stay after the college timings, as a lot of television ad film shootings take place in the campus, so you can now imagine how good the location and the infrastructure would be. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'college has a really good infra ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Infosys, Tech Mahindra, Accenture and Syntel are the major recruiters at Thakur College of Engineering. Average salary must be around Rs. 2.5 lac/year. Placement records over the last few years have been close to 100%. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'one of the worst training and placement cell across engineering colleges in Mumbai. Don''t Expect a job from here instead you should Apply off campus, that will help you much more. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET) is located in the beautiful Thakur Village which is 15-20 minutes by rickshaw from Kandivli station (W. Rly.) Students usually prefer to go by bus because it’s quite far from the station and hence rickshaw becomes a bit expensive for daily commuting. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'if you come to college via bikes .... then u''ll might get free dirt rides daily... mostly during monsoon...and if travelling by buses then u''ll njoy the experience of bursting popcorn...and the bad news is that ther are 2 principal''s especially in extc branch. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Excellent canteen. Very roomy but gets completely occupied as it is shared by students of all the faculties. Great food nevertheless. Students especially love the seating arrangement that has been done very thoughtfully and typical lounge style chairs have been provided. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Canteen is best place to hang out with presence of eye popping chicks sweetie. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Pizza Hut, CCD, Colassa (Hukkah Joint/Chinese Food), Monarch Restaurant, Jumbo King Vada Pav are all close to Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET). Dominos, Nirvana and some excellent hangouts in Kandivali Lokhandwala are also very famous. Thakur Cinema and Kulraj Broadway is the place where you''ll find most of the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'A mix breed of crowd - fun loving as well as nerds - students blend well though. Entertaining, decent and fun-to-have life. Majority are, however, not much interested in studies though the scene is changing since a few years. Being located in the western suburbs, students from locations like Navi Mumbai and Central/Harbour Mumbai aren''t particularly keen about joining Thakur College is big numbers. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Crowd of here is the "worst"... poor knowledge students.. the college works on the name of professor Ravish Singh only... bad placement... bad marks ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET) celebrates Zephyr (Technical Festival) in odd semesters, Sojourn (Cultural Festival) in even semesters. They also have a Sports Festival. Great atmosphere during the festivals. Students have a gala time. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET) is very strict in attendance matters. Minimum requirement is 60%. Students lingering around at Thakur Cinema if caught are sent to classrooms forcefully, of course that''s only during college hours. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'attendance is compulsory 75% but you can get away with less than that.Just be nice to the profs and respect them in class, you wont have any problems as such. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'Location and infrastructure adds charm to Thakur College of Engineering and Technology (TCET). The faculty is good yet the students here aren’t so keen on studying. So, a mixed reaction for this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Thakur College of Engineering and Technology', 'DO NOT ENTER IN EXTC DEPARTMENTITS ONE OF THE WORST BUT COMP and I.T. DEPARTMENT are BEST ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Majority of the teachers are freshers with only few Phd’s completing the teaching staff. Almost all the teachers communicate in Hindi. The good part for the students is that they are extremely co-operative. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Facility is ok but students say fees is too much as compared to facility. Students are allowed to go out of the college during college hours but teachers can''t step out as if they are in jail ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'The building is under construction. Last benches face a waterfall everyday. Labs are well furnished with internet access. The campus has a lawn and a huge playground. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'fully bakwaas collegeage... there is nothng inside and outside of the campus which creates interest... I woander what the management is doing since last 3 years! they hvnt even completed the building yet. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'The first batch is yet to come out and nothing can be commented about the placements till then. ', 'Anonymous'),
