('Theem College of Engineering', 'The college is situated in Boisar east and is around 4 kms from Boisar Railway station. Share rickshaw’s cost you Rs. 10- per person. College provides facilities for buses which run from the college to Boisar Railway station. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Travelling is the big problem here as there are only trains after 1 hr and that too is rushed. There is no local trains to boisar to add to the problems and there is no hostel facilities near to college the faculty is bad ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'The canteen is quite spacious but, the less said about the food, the better. Non-vegetarians get lucky only on Wednesday and Friday. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'haveing a great time here... everything is good except Canteen... but I love it ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Chinese food parlour outside the college where most of the students spent their lives. Chinchi and Kelve beach are the scenic ones accompanied with Mamacha Gaav and Surya Dam. KT theatre and Gold are for the movie buffs. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Not very strict. Below 65-70%, parents get a call but they aren’t called to college. Students have to pay some amount as fine when they fall short of attendance. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Jashn'' Theem is the combined cultural and technical fest, held in the 1st week of Feb ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Muslim minority. The college has students from all over Mumbai. Students, especially boys, are often heard complaining ‘yaaar! Ladkiyaan bahut kam hai’ ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'college is good but the principal is ok. Students say he wants fine if attendance is less as if he only wants money from students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'Faculty is friendly and attendance is lenient but location and crowd always remain a major issue. It should be one of your last choices. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Theem College of Engineering', 'All I would like to say "yuckz!!!!" guys run for your life, worst experience/decision I ever had/took in my life was to go for this college, life is so dull here in this college :/, it''s so irritating when light goes off in every few hours. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Faculty is so so. Some have deep knowledge. Some with no interest in teaching, haveing superficial knowledge and interested in college politics only. Faculty to transfers after every 3-4 years. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'i have heard that the faculty is now not so good. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Huge campus. Infra Old but has a heritage touch ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'The campus of VJTI is huge, one might even get lost initially. Lots of open space, a cricket and a football field, tennis courts and basketball court are available for recreational activities. However the buildings being old, the classrooms and the labs are not places you’ll enjoy being in. “You’ll get baked to death in the heat during the summers”, says a second year Mechanical student. Many instruments in labs are old which often fail to function properly. You can access internet from computer labs whenever you wish. Wi-Fi connectivity has been promised but not been installed yet. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'and none can beat vjti in placement..among mumbai unversity ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'this is just not a good institute as compare to the IIT''s and NIT''s.AND who said DJ that avg salary package is more than six lakhs.....its just less than 3 lakhs .check it out on the official website of vjti:www.vjti.ac.in/TPO/TPO.asp ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute, popular as VJTI, is an esteemed autonomous government engineering institute located in central Mumbai. It is just a 5 minute drive or 12-15 minute walk from Dadar (W. Rly and C. Rly.), Matunga (C. Rly.), Wadala (Harbour Rly.) and King’s Circle (Harbour Rly.) stations. Number of BEST buses plying from all parts of Mumbai is also a good option to reach the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'i am in first year now for mech ...and i am living in vjti hostel... guys its worst hostel i had ever seen...... and im getting very bore here,,,,,, ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'VJTI is a really good collegeage. I don''t think teaching is a problem there. its true its not as it was few years ago, fir bhi you can easily survive 4 years here. and hostels are not that bad, you will really enjoy hostel life there ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Canteen: Normal. Edible food. Not an issue! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'The canteen has changed!! Its awesome now!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Various restaurants in Matunga and among favourites are Mani’s Idli, Sherry’s Rolls and Frankies (best and the cheapest), Garnish, Classic, Relax, etc. There’s Only Parathas and Madras Café for those who eat only in ''elite'' restaurants. CCD is also close by. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Also crowd is much better than the other MU colleges. (maybe leaving aside DJ.Sanghvi)It has the best extra-curricular activites and its a dream college for the robotics and automation people. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', '50% crowd is awsome....great miands ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'Festivals: Rocking! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'The best part about VJTI is the awesome fests it holds every year and the over-ENTHUsiastic crowd. These are the best held fests for enginneering colleges in Mumbai. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'attendance is not really a bother as long as you are not in civil :PTeachers actually call your parents if you bunk lectures in civil dept ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'At VJTI, Civil branch is very strict about attendance. For other branches, it is not much of an issue, on a simple condition that you do not spoil your relations with the professors. “Panga mat lena mere dost” says a final year Computers student. However, there are always exceptions and you have to identify those professors and attend their lectures regularly. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'excuse me IITB..it is quite obvious that IITB is much better than VJTI.comparison goes between colleges in MU and VJTI..but you must be very stupid to post a comment here despising VJTI and favouring IITBsuch comments wont help anyone to decide which college to choose on the basis on CET score (and not JEE score LOL) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute', 'It''s a must go ..FACULTY -5.0INFRA- 4.0ACCESSIBILIY - 4.0AMENITIES - 4.0FESTS - 5.0TECHNICAL EXPOSURE - 4.0HANGOUTS - 2.0CROWD - 3.5 (They are nerds) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Some of the experienced teaching faculty that Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) had before. have left the college. The other old and senior teaching faculties are extremely good but there are a few freshers (passed out students), who are not up to the mark. Professors are co-operative. Because of the association with Vidyalankar classes the faculty is experienced in teaching and industry demands. Notes of Vidyalankar coaching classes are distributed to all students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'college is very great and its teaching staff is very helpfulOne of the best teachers were first the teachers of this college like Dubey Sir of Mechanics and Engineering. drwinPowar Sir of BEEVelenker Sir of CPAnkur Sir of EDCPhatak Sir of Mathsand a very supporting and students caring Principal....Seema Shah Mam ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'If you visit Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) for the first time, you’ll think it’s a MALL (I mean it). You can''t make out where the classrooms are because the classrooms don''t look like classrooms from outside.. There is an amphitheatre which is visible from any corner of the engineering building. Laboratories are in the basement.Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) shares the campus with Vidyalankar Polytechnic and Vidyalankar School of Information Technology. The campus comprises 3 buildings, 2 gardens, a football field, a volleyball ground and also a cricket pitch. Also, separate parking lots are available for students and faculty members, for both 2-wheelers and 4-wheelers. A new building called the X-Block is also under construction, which has already been featured in an international architecture e-magazine. Hostel facilities are also available. The new M-block for Management students has facilities like smoke detectors, sprinklers. (BEWARE SMOKERS)!The library provides a wide ranging collection of books which include university prescribed text books and reference material. The library also subscribes to all major international journals and magazines. Some major non-technical magazines are also subscribed to. The library also has a reading hall which is open 6 days a week and on Sundays when exams are approaching.So, by and large, excellent infrastructure. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'the infrastructure is awesome .............only the bad thing is that it is surrouanded by slums but inside the campus its very good environment ... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Placements at Vidyalankar are quite decent, mainly because of the contacts the college administration has within the industry. Infosys and Patni pick the maximum students. Infosys has selected Vidyalankar as a partner for its Campus-Connect Program, wherein they train Pre-final year Vidyalankar students to make them industry ready.Average salaries range around Rs.3 lac p.a. to Rs. 3.5 lac p.a. for BTech students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Campus selection/placements are great every year. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) is located in central Mumbai, and can be easily reach from all parts of the city. It takes about 15 minutes to walk from Wadala station (Harbour Rly.) to the institute. Also it''s not all that far from Dadar station (W.Rly. and C.Rly.). Buses can drop you very close to the college. Share taxis from Wadala west also take you to the college.There are ample of buses which ply between Dadar and Wadala, so a good option for central and western students also. However, it is surrounded by slums which is a huge turn off. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Travelling is an issue initially, but you''ll get used to. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'A canteen and a cafe both offer a wide range of food and beverages. Food is edible and moderately cheap. VITs campus has a striking eatery outlet - ''snack in d box''. Food is reasonable in the canteen and in the café, starting from Rs. 20 to a maximum of Rs. 60, but ''snack in d box'' is comparatively costlier. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'you get good quality food and are cheap rates in the canteen. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Difficult to find good places out here because the location is slightly secluded. Dosti Acres is real close, so if you manage to find friends from that complex in your college, you can have good time there. Also the IMAX theatre is not very far. Last but not the least is Five Gardens. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'don''t worry about hangout places,because you won''t need any.. Cafeteria is best for tp with friends (Or anywhere within building,afterall its a MALL).New thing started last semester ''Coffee Day'' ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Crowd at Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) is the general middle class one. Lots of weirdos with their own weird sets of ideas and thoughts are found here. But then again that is the case with many engineering colleges. VIT strongly opposes ragging and also has its own anti-ragging committee, a trend started in many other engineering colleges also. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'I oppose that crowd is average..college has good crowd..many of students cme from good location like Dadar,Bandra,Colaba...and many more..SO vit is changing.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) celebrates an inter-collegiate technical festival, FERVOR, an intra-collegiate cultural festival, VERVE, and an inter-collegiate sports festival are held in the college campus around February/March. The highlight of the sports festival is the S6 (Six a side - Six overs) cricket tournament in which more than 15 colleges participate. It also includes intra-collegiate competitions in volleyball, box-cricket, throwball, carrom, chess etc. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Attendance at Vidyalankar Institute of Technology (VIT) is not quite an issue. No extra assignments or any such action is taken against defaulters. However, some teachers who want to show that they should be given more importance might cause minor glitches by reducing the term work marks of defaulters. So, it would be wise to be cautious of such teachers. Most of the teaching and non-teaching staff are extremely friendly and helpful but there are a few exceptions, you need to attend those certain lectures. So, it would be wise to be cautious of such teachers. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'Moderately strict, mainly depends on who FE incharge is!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'A typical engineering college where crowd is average. Though there aren’t many places to hangout, the college has typical amenities which makes it distinct from others. Generally cut-offs are at an average score. This may be credited with the fact that college has more seats and being non-minority institution adds further to lower cut-offs. The college has good placement records for the last couple of years. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyalankar Institute of Technology', 'VERY BAD college!!! I HATE IT HERE!! GET ME OUT!!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'The teaching staff at Vartak college of Engineering is decent and has a command on their language and knows their subject quite well. On the whole an above average faculty. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Faculty are in contrast between average and below average.. pretty high number of freshers. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'It’s a five storey building with quite a decent campus. But as the crowd isn’t great, the campus is usually empty. It has a good vehicle parking space. The classrooms aren’t appealing and the fans are said to not work sometimes as well. The laboratories are without AC’s which is one of the biggest drawbacks during summers. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'college has huge parking slot but doesn''t have good playground.. and the average college not the best one but not the worst also....!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'It is said that the placements aren’t 100%. The companies recruiting students in the streams like EXTC, Computers and Mechanical are really good. The rest are said to face some problems. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'placements are also not so bad ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Vidyavardhini’s College of Engineering and Technology (VCET) popularly known as Vartak college is located in sVasai. It is a couple of steps away from from Vasai railway station; hence no issue of spending for rickshaws and the BEST buses. The Gurudwara and the Jain temple are the best landmarks to the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Location of VCET is very good. Only 5 minute walking distance from Vasai stn. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'The canteen at Vartak college of Engineering is OKAY. The food variety isn’t too much and the cost is also high. Your home-made dabba will be a smart choice. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Canteen is pretty good but the food here is worst. Low variety of overpriced food. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Various food outlets like Domino''s and Garcia''s pizza, Andy''s Burger and roadside food stalls have cropped up near the college. You can also expect to meet all your college buddies in the very famous KT cinema which is close to the college. The other enjoyments are very far from the college which would amount to like a one-day trip. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'best college for instrumentation!!now you can even hangout @ dominos,garcias,naturals,baskin and robbins,andys burger king etc!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Vartak College of Engineering doesn’t have any quota so there is no majority of a particular caste here. Since the college is located really far in the Northern suburbs, most of the students are from the western and North Central suburbs. Overall crowd is said to be serious and not fun-loving which spoils the enjoyment section of four years of engineering. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'I agree that the crowd is serious,but only when it comes 2 studies.....otherwise you can spend 4 yrs wid your sweet friends formd from all dept in FE ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Cultural festival: Zeal (Feb-Mar)Technical festival: Orion (Sept-Oct) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Zeal festival is more than awesome. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Very strict. 75% is a MUST. Moreover, if the attendance is low, the college authority makes you write a NOTE which puts a compulsion on you that next time the attendance has to improve, else some SERIOUS action. Parents, too, are said to have been called many times. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'The academic activitious taken strictly..no chances for putting proxies/below 75% attendance...But faculties are somehow stuents-friendly..as they don''t put such restrictions on you. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'Vidyavardhini College of Engieering and Technology comes out to be one of the finest colleges in the Far-north-west region of Mumbai as far as academics is concerned. But it''s difficult to say because of lack of better colleges around or because of the college''s own qualities. Crowd, location and hangouts are a huge turn off. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vidyavardhini''s College of Engineering and Technology', 'AC`s do work in Labs. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Faculty at Viva Institute of Technology is not bad, average. Although most of them don’t have much experience in teaching and are only fresher, they manage to teach well somehow. The experienced professors are very good. Faculties for Electrical are the best of all. For EXTC, Civil and Mechanical too faculty is good except that they''re strict in EXTC. Some of the teachers are rude and egoistic but most of them are helpful and understanding. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Some of the faculty has no manners to speak with students as well as their parents.Rest is quite good or students may get used to the problems. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'There are two college buildings, one of which is still under construction even after quite a few years since its inception. One building houses classrooms, libary, teacher''s room, administation et cetera and the other one is used mainly for labs and workshop. Labs for Civil, Mechanical and Computers are good but Electrical don''t have any and those students have to conduct their experiments in other departments'' laboratories. Their library is poorly lit and students never feel like studying there. Surprisingly there is a well equipped gymnasium cum gymkhana. Wi-fi internet is available but students don''t get to use it too often either due to connectivity issues or due to not getting permission. Infrastructure is still developing but at very sluggish pace and students often wonder where does the money paid by them as fees go, if not in infrastructure? ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'The WiFi also has been blocked for few months. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'The placements for first batch (passed in 2013) were disappointing. Very few companies came for campus recruitment. Hence only a handful of students were able to bag jobs and that too in local cos. like Raw Engineering and Parekh Aluminium. No placements for Electrical department. Average salary was around 1.5 Lakh and highest was 1.8 Lakh per annum. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'No expectations from college campus i.e companies who are giving nano packages + nano jobs. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Viva Institute of Technology (VIoT) is located in the northern extreme suburb of Mumbai on western railways – i.e Virar. It is in a a slighly hilly village called Shirgaon, and college is surrounded by beautiful greenery on all sides. It is about 7.5 km from Virar railway station and reaching here is very inconvenient as public transport namely ST buses make you wait too long and rickshaws in this region do not follow meter, hence are very costly. College buses to and from Virar Station are available at specific timings. Most people seem to use them due to lack of other decent commuting options. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Travelling is like hell on strikes. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'It is a very small canteen and seating arrangement is also quite poor. There are only a few tables and its accompanying chairs for over 1000 people from different courses offered on the same campus like engineering, MBA, science, pharmacy and architecture. So it gets invariably crammed up during break. At other times too it is overcrowded. Luckily quality and taste of food is decent enough. And there are whole lot of variety on the menu as well. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Canteen as always is the worst, small and totally unhygienic. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Sadly there are NO hangouts for around the college as it is located in a remote, rural area. Nature lovers will rejoice as there are some hillocks, a dam, many trees and never ending fields around the college. And yes, a western cafe (local tapri) is newly opened outside the college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Majority of the students come from urban areas. Most of them also come from the North-Mumbai. There are hardly anyone coming from beyond Andheri on western line. The crowd is pretty decent. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Hiteshi is cultural festival and each department conducts its own technical fest. Most students see them as a mere formality and only a handful of them truly participate. Support from staff and management is also meagre. However, their sports week is a big hit among students and good ammount of participation is seen. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'fest is also below average, besides in jan-feb there''s a sports week organized, which is pretty good. ', 'Anonymous');
INSERT INTO `collegereviews` (`CollegeName`, `Reviews`, `User`) VALUES
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'College is strict with attendance. 75% is a must. Else you term work marks are at stake. To score full attendance marks you have attend more than 90% of the lectures. Anything below 75% and you are in for trouble.Apart from strict attendance there are some weird disciplinary rules are in place such as - you can''t wear round neck tees nor can you wear printed ones and slippers/flip-flops are not allowed. These rules are followed strictly. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'attendance must be 75% ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'Viva Institute of Technology (VIoT) is a comparatively a new college. Good faculty is favourable factor but there are many more adverse factors like accessibility and placements. However, students studying here are hopeful that things will improve over time. Those scoring below average in entrance exam usually opt for this college. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Viva Institute of Technology', 'bakwaas college... only stupids go to this college.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'There’s not much to say about the faculty of Vivekanand Education Society’s Institute of Technology (VESIT) as its just the same like any other engineering college, some professors are excellent and the remaining are just about average. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'A bugged up college. Half the faculty can''t even speak proper english...let alone teach in the said medium. All you get from most profs are the same ppts that they have been using for generations now. Not to mention a mafia type nexus of certain professors: if one doesn''t like you, the rest will screw you.and how do the students commute from the station to the new (slum) campus?..swim I suppose.I''ll bet the college would have donned a new look (rather disguises), given that the accreditation guys are on their way. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'The college has recently moved into the new campus and the infrastructure is pretty awesome now. Each department has different floors with huge and well-equipped labs. New and efficient PCs have been brought in and the students seem to be very happy with the performance of the super-fast computers.The only downside of the new campus is the pungent smell which is perennial throughtout the day. After a few days students do get used to it. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'campus is also good... and the college is trying hard to maintain the cleanliness.... the college ground is yet to be made ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Great records at VESIT. 100 % placement in top IT companies. Microsoft picks up 4-5 students sometimes. Average salaries is a good Rs. 3 lac/year with maximum salary even going upto Rs. 8.5 lac/year. For academic year 2011, multinational companies like Deloitte, JP Morgan and Nomura picked up around 20 students each. Microsoft took around 10, Morgan Stanley - 2 and GE - 10. And companies like BPCL, HPCL and Honeywell also visit the campus. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'placements are good but pretty bad teaching and who is this spreading rumours that extc is best dept(4 saal mein toh aisa laga nahi)..look i did the mistake..i dont want you to do it..if you are getting into vesit be prepared for the worst..and if you are comin from general category you have better options like vjti,spit(chalega if you compromise in selecting branch..it aint matter in placements) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Nearest station from Vivekanand Education Society’s Institute of Technology (VESIT) fondly known as “Swami”, is Kurla (C. Rly. and Harbour Rly.) about 1-2 km from college. So, assuming you get a rick immediately, you should reach the college within 10 minutes. The new campus is located in Collectors Colony, Chembur. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'the new campus which is in collectors colony ,chembur has an awesome c shaped grand bulding. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Since the time the college has moved to the new campus, the canteen at VESIT seems to be pretty much appealing in terms of ambience and food. A lot of variety in food is available and at extremely low prices. So its quite light on the pocket, and you wouldn’t really mind the ambience after that. Oh, and there are three canteens. *Huge Smile* ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'the sad thing about the college is the canteen it''s like naam bade darshan choote they can''t even make a tasty vada pav. but anyways college is good. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'McDonald’s is nearby which is the favourite among the students, Barista, CCD, Dominos, Ambrosia, Baskin Robins, Acres Club, Cream Centre are among other options available next to Swami ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Although the crowd looks a lot more refreshing as compared to engineering standards, it''s certainly nerdy. People are more inclined towards studies which ultimately does pay them off, because they get excellent results. Bunking and hanging out is usually avoided because it''s difficult to find those kind of students here. There''s a minority quota for Sindhis. Eventhough located on the Harbour/Central line, students from various other parts of the city join this is reputed institute. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'siandhi quota increased from 20 % to 50 %. Due to this placements may hamper in coming 4 yrs. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'There are events all round the year at Vivekanand Education Society’s Institute of Technology (VESIT) from robotics to debates. There are three societies which conduct such events after college hours. Receives good participation.College has one techfest called Praxis, one cultural fest Utsav, and Sports Fest Sphurti, which also receive amazing response from the students. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Hey guys I''m in second year in this college.Really it''s awesome, VESIT cricket league, VESIT premiere league, Illusion, Spurti, Praxis, Utsav are the events going round the clock whole year.Cricket league, premiere league and Illusion which is a cultural event have4 been introduced this year.Also it''s not strict at all ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Attendance is strict. It’s not a problem for majority of the people at VESIT because if you have 65 % attendance (which most of people here manage) there are absolutely no issues, below which they generally call your parents for a small visit. Some students are detained, very rarely though. But at the same time your term-work is screwed equally. “But not at all as strict as its known to be!”, says one of their student (you also get some idea about the crowd from his statement). ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Yes the college is a bit strict with attendance but they don''t take actions. Just warning, at least for 1st year. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'Vivekanand Education Society’s Institute of Technology (VESIT) is excellent in terms of studies and placements. Excellent infrastructure adds as a plus point to the college. It must be one of the top 5 on the priority list. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Vivekanand Education Society''s Institute of Technology', 'I''ve been here. take my advice, if given another choice opt for it. Don''t make a mistake. *All that glitters is not gold*If you still are stubborn and want to go to the ''best'' college, just remember my name every time you curse yourself for the 3-4 years you will be in engineering looking at other students enjoy. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'The faculty at Watumull is a mixture. Some are good and experienced while there are a few who are ordinary too. The computers faculty is nice, but it is a bit strict. The biomedical faculty is like a school faculty. The faculty of the instrumentation branch is Ok. One faculty worth mentioning is of the EXTC branch. The EXTC has very good professors. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'along with that the teaching staff is quite experienced and then passing rate is also good compared to others...It has been a very satisfying experience ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology functions from a single eight-storey building, which underwent renovation sometime back and plans are afoot to add another two floors to the building for additional laboratories and other facilities. The college has no open grounds. However, it does have other sporting facilities for playing table tennis, football, cricket, chess and carrom. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'There is 90% placement this year, Companies like Patni, Infosys, JP morgan, Accenture, CapeGemini, Sudherland, Blue star(biomedical core), Sanrad international(biomedical), Tech Mahiandra,GE IT, LandT, LandT IES, Cactus communication, CMC etc have recruited students from watumull this year, and it seems progressing in coming future.and as of every year, this year also watumull has university rankers from biomedical department. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Around 70% students are placed every year out of a total of 210 students. However, the placements are in good companies like LandT, CapGemini, Tech Mahindra, Geodesic etc. with decent salaries (Average salary: Rs. 2.5 lac p.a.) ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'The location of this college also rocks. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology is located at Worli, a posh locality in south Mumbai. It has an incredible location on the Worli seaface, with its imposing structure towering over the Arabian Sea. It can reached by BEST buses which are available from all parts of the city. Closest railway station is Lower Parel (W.Rly.) about 10-15 minutes by taxi. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'The canteen at Watumull is very nice. The food is very tasty and cheap too. The canteen is not very spacious, so as to accommodate all the students during the lunch break, but students somehow manage. The canteen is a good place for people who like to dig into chinese food.A special mention : Triple schezwan rice made by Shiva!! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Canteen is not spacious ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Worli Seaface, Mafco, Atria mall and various other restaurants around. “Mela” serves good food but is a bit expensive. Spices and Flavours is another good option. Phoenix mills is a fantastic option, but it is a little far. There is great roll/frankly point right outside the main gate, which is very famous, you might want to try that out too. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'The crowd rocks. It is quite nice. Everyone is down to earth and quite co-operative and fun-loving. Well, there are a few exceptions, but those are obviously there everywhere. If you are lucky enough you will get good company. There are some groups who come from the same junior college, so getting into those could be difficult. Overall, you will have four pretty pleasant years. Also, the college has plenty of special days every now and then. Traditional, rose, chocolate, stripes, and many more. Life is enjoyable. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'instrumentation crowd is awesome...lif wid them is enjoyable...otherwise some crowd of computer and bio are like school crowd...cryin babies...however ther are exceptions....you mit find some crowd kanjus also and mannerless....so its really hard to get a good company here. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Watumull College holds an annual festival, ENSEMBLE, which highlights the achievements of the college and its students. It is generally held after the conclusion of the first term of the year. It consists of events like rappelling, wall-climbing, robotics, a virtual stock exchange, mock detective games, treasure hunts, base games, crystal mazes and various personality contests.Another College Fest held by Watumull is WIFI. It is a popular intercollegiate fest and is conducted every year around September. But the festival lets the college down as no technical events happen, but people attend just to play football. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'Attendance is quite strict. Attendance is verified orally even after signing so giving proxies is difficult...sickening!! Some professors don’t allow you to attend practicals if you don’t attend their lectures. If your attendance is really low they just send a letter at home and call parents. It actually varies from professor to professor and also on their mood. If you have a bad image, some professors like to trouble you during submissions. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'attendance is compulsory which sucked but you better attend if you want to maintain good gpa and have any MS plans. I didn''t attend and eanded up writing tons of impositions. Lost my file and had to write it again (Totally my fault. Not blaming anyone) So yeah life sucked and I was regretting coming here but made some decent friends that I couldn''t care less about. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'this us quiet good college........but not that...... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Watumull Institute of Electronic Engineering and Computer Technology', 'very good atmospheregood crowd ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Most of the teachers at Xavier Instiute of Engineering (XIE) are good but there are a few horrible exceptions. The fresh graduates who have taken up teaching are really pathetic. The best faculty is in EXTC and IT departments. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'few horrible teachers ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'The infrastructure Xavier Institute of Engineering is not very satisfactory. The college ground is big enough to play all sports. Majority of the lab equipments work properly. Classooms are in decent conditon. Libraries have desired number of books. Lack of lush green plantations is a big thumbs down to such a huge campus. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'The moment you enter this life-sucking heck-hole of a college you will start to feel like the fishermen and slum lords inhabiting the surrouanding areas.The "gymkhana" is a closed room full of moss and traces of fungus. If you want to get married, I''m pretty sure the principal will let you have the ground, cause some Tom, Dick or Harry seems to have his wedding on the college ground every other day. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', '60% of the students get placed. Tech Mahindra takes maximum students. Patni, Infosys, Accenture and Quinox are the other major companies. The placements and salaries offered are just about average. It is said that Panasonic recruited a student from EXTC and offered 12 lakh p.a.. Hope it''s true. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Placement is OK compared to quality of teaching ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Xavier Institute of Engineering is 15 minutes by foot from Mahim railway station (W. Rly. And Harbour Rly.) However, the roads are very dusty and there is a traffic jam always so it is very irritating to walk. But with no other option, one has to suffer everyday while coming from and going to college. The other option is to come by bus, again a 15 minute walk on foot from Mahim bus depot. A few buses do drop you right in front of the college but their frequency really sucks. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'The canteen is small and there is too less variety of food to offer. XAVIER’s MANAGEMENT, if you ever happen to read this, please do something about it. The prices are economical though. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Don''t ever try to eat in the canteen, you''ll most probably meet fried cockroach someday. You better go and eat in the next lane. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Only one word, “Bandra”. There is nothing much in Mahim so the students usually head to Bandra which is nearby. Innumerable places to go once you reach Bandra. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'There are many Christians because of the Christian quota at Xavier Engineering College. Overall the crowd is good and you won’t realize where time went by. Four years of engineering can be easily dealt with. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'The cultural festival of Xavier Institute of Engineering is “Spandan” and the technical festival is “Transmission”. They are usually held in February in alternate years. So, effectively only one festival to have fun every year. SIGH! ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Talking of festivals, they are OK except for some restrictions from management. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'The principal has started the system of sending letters at home and threatens to detain students who bunk regularly. As long as you keep it above 70% there should be no problems. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'Xavier Engineering College is definitely not your first choice but it is a better option than the colleges which are far away from Mumbai if you don’t manage to get into the top colleges. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Xavier Institute of Engineering', 'dont take admission here........... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Average for all departments. Majority are said to be junior professors with little experience. “They wish to help and are very kind-hearted, but aren’t able to, perhaps due to a lack of experience”, quotes one student. Some of the students have complained that faculty is so bad that they can not rely on them at all and look for succour in coaching classes. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'at start of Engineering we were proud of the bus facility but now it is in worse coandition... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'bus system is good.. infrastructure is improving.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Now days college is really improving, tennis court, basketball court, swimming pool, new canteen, cafeteria. Awesome.Fest really awesome. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', '“Zero, only offered placement as a teacher in the same college” says one students sadly, before blending with the darkness. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'last it got 20 companies for placement...it will increase ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology (YTIET) is located about 1.5kms from Bhivpuri Railway station on the CST- Karjat route (Central Rly). There is no problem in terms of accessibility after you reach the station, since the college bus facility is very well managed. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'only 3 buses come to pick at the morning...worst college... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'The canteen is “cheap”. Food is inedible and only a handful of students are found munching on food here. Some of the students suspect adulteration in soft drinks. Water tastes bad. One of them exaggeratedly says, “Ulti bhi nahi hoti ab to”. The canteen is named ''Renaissance'', but has nothing to do with the name. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'canteen is not as bad as written here... its good.. now they have also provided water cooler and purifier... and there is also chai and chocolate for good quality food coffee etc. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'There is nothing near the college except for farms, hills and a river with no water. Most of the students prefer to hangout inside the college campus itself at something known as “Mushroom huts”. Others just leave for home.During monsoon students sometimes go to the famous "Bhivpuri Waterfalls". ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Chai and Chocolate is amazing for its cold coffee.... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'The crowd here is a mix of both fun-loving and studious. Majority of the students come from Central suburbs like Kalyan, Dombivali and Badlapur. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'About crowd - maximum student come from Kalyan thane dadar western mumbai.. less student from ambernath badlapur ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology (YTIET) celebrates its Technical Festival – Area 244 in February-end. The students very fond of this fest and have a good time. The cultural festival Crystal is held in March-end. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'even their technical fest rocked in 2012 ''TURBOTECK 2K12''... ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'Strict in the first year, wherein 75% is made compulsory. For the other years it shows some leniency and not much action is taken till about 40-50%, except for donation of books to the library or a nominal punishment. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'don''t see comments of 2012.. college has improved so much in back 2 years.. see reviews of 2014 you will find the improvement ', 'Anonymous'),
('Yadavrao Tasgaonkar Institute of Engineering and Technology', 'overall this college is better than any other college from back side.. ', 'Anonymous'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'College provides a decent environment for students.', 'Ghanshyam'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'It is not overall bad college', 'ash'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'College is average.', 'Ghanshyam'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'Nice college', 'Ghanshyam'),
('Sardar Patel Institute of Technology', 'This college is good faculty wise', 'Ghanshyam');
